The paper proposes a method to improve object counting from images using class activation map visualizations and regulating activation maps. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The method also involves machine learning techniques such as regression models and neural networks, which are covered in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance improvements achieved through the proposed method, which is related to machine learning evaluation and optimization, falling under the machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which is also related to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
